The paper proposes a neural point process model that jointly models event sequences and time series data. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI) as it utilizes recurrent neural networks to model the data. The attention mechanism used in the model also suggests a focus on interpretability and explainability, which could place it in the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on modeling complex processes and network dynamics could also place it in the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
